<title>SRI LANKA: Ceylon Tobacco up on good profit forecast.</title>
<headline>Ceylon Tobacco up on good profit forecast.</headline>
<dateline>COLOMBO 1997-01-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares of Ceylon Tobacco Co Ltd rose 5.83 percent or 1.75 rupees, to 31.75 on Tuesday on expectation of improved profits, brokers said.</p>
<p>&quot;Investors are collecting the share because they expect profits in the last quarter to December 31, 1996 to be good,&quot; a local broker said.</p>
<p>Ceylon Tobacco, Sri Lanka's monopoly cigarette maker, is a subsidiary of BAT Industries Plc.</p>
<p>-- Colombo newsroom (941) 434319</p>
